text: This song is my therapy that I turn to every time I remember my previous cats. Itâ€™s my only remedy after my five experiences, each of which ended in losing them all. Thank you, Seungmin, chan and Han, for this wonderful song that fills me with different emotions and makes me feel that I am not alone. author: @Kowwchy
text:
this song quite literally brings me to tears. my special girl passed away last year and i listened to this song on repeat for a while, for as sad as it made me, it also brought comfort and joy in remembering the good times i had with her. after some months i came back to this song and all the tears and emotions came flooding back. 

today, my other dog passed away, ironically the same day that SKZ performed their dominATE Sydney show (which i of course still went to - i needed some cheering up). while a small part of me was hoping i'd hear this live, i'm also very very glad that i didn't burst into tears in a fully packed stadium.  

tldr; this song holds a very special place in my heart <3

author: @diagoart3805
text:
I keep coming here again and again, everytime I feel like I need to let some emotions out. I used to go cry to my dog when I was feeling particularly bad and she always comforted me and let me pet her as long as I needed even though he wasn't the most fond of touch other times. It's been three and a half years since she ran on the rainbow tinted trail somewhere I can't reach and I still miss her every day.
Thank you so much for this song, it means the world to me. I just wish it was officially released to other platforms as well so I could listen to it even more. I'll keep hoping and will keep on listening here in the meantime.

author: @youngestkittenlady
text:
Today marked 1 whole Year of my life without my Soulcat Oreo ğŸ¥ºğŸ•Šï¸âœ¨ğŸ’« Bhadra 7th in Nepali Date calendar , marked full 1 year of you not being on earth Oreo. You got your wings on Bhadra 7th, 2080 (August 24th, 2023) at 9 am. Your last day on earth. You took your last few deep breaths with me, your eyes were watching me saying that last goodbye. Happy 1 Year in Heaven my love Oreo. 
Dear Oreo, It's been 365 days without you here with us. Time surely flies but grief never ends.
You shared your 5 Years and 7 months with us and left all us scattered with deepest loss and grief without an expiry date. As I'm writing this, my eyes are watering and tears are falling without me knowing . Although I don't cry daily for you now as I used to, that doesn't mean my grief ended or so the longing and love for you. This is why I see your pictures daily to remind myself that you're forever here with me, you're living within me in my heart and soul.
Each day of these 365 days without you here , there isn't a time if I haven't mentioned your name or talked about you or remembered you Oreo. As I'm typing this on my phone, I still can see your picture on my keyboard background which gives me sense of solace and peace. Back me 365 days before , couldn't have ever imagined my life without you. I have had witnessed many deaths of cats kittens as being a foster mom, but witnessing you Oreo, your eyes slowly leaving the earth, becoming dull, the heartbeat becoming slower and slower to completely stopping, everything hurts and is engraved in my mind and eyes. Yet I assure myself, that you choose me to witness your final moments, being in my arms gives me hope to hold on.
Full 365 days (1 Year) has been going by holding on. Holding on to meet you again at rainbow bridge. Holding on thinking you're with Suru, our angel Stray mom cat, and the other foster kittens Demian, Tiger, Mystic and Hope whose life's ended short and Raven too who went to heaven before 2 days of you leaving this earth. And our stray dog Ratey who left this earth back on 2023. We will all meet up again together at the rainbow bridge. I know saying this and actually believing is different. But believing this also doesn't mean your pain and grief will be gone. It just gives us strength, peace and solace by holding on. All the pains and suffering are gone where you're right now. Those who don't believe will say people are crazy when they say their beloved pets visited them from heaven and gave signs. But if believed truly by heart, it does works.
Oreo, thank you for giving me signs always. Whether it's me seeing you in my dreams, or seeing a heart shaped cloud, or clouds shaped as cats, or seeing butterflies, or seeing white feathers,or seeing any cats or kittens which slightly resemble you and your marking. I have documented all, written all on notes, pictures and videos everything. I hope, no I truly believe you're at peace now. You're resting well with no pain, fear and suffering. I have been honouring you Oreo always. Honouring you by feeding the strays, honouring you by sharing all those 5 Years and 7 months memorable moments you have shared with us together, honouring you by writing about you, honouring you by printing your pictures on bags, cushions, sliver bracelet so that I can always see and remember your cute little face forever. Not only honouring you but doing this things have given me solace and peace past 365 days of me grieving. Writing this here, because Hold On truly gives me solace and peace ğŸ¥ºğŸ•Šï¸âœ¨ğŸ’«ğŸŒˆOreo Forever ğŸŒˆğŸ’«âœ¨January 15th 2018 till August 24th 2023 ğŸŒˆ

author: @Withlovefrmstranger
text:
LETTER FOR SEUNGMIN.  U Â´á´¥` U
...
Dear Seungmin,
When I read your special mention of the 1-year anniversary of "Hold On" on Bubble, I was intrigued and decided to give the song a listen, as it felt like this song holds a special place in your heart. [I am just 50-day-old admirer of Stray Kids (and your voice) and still diligently exploring the previous content.]
.
Firstly, I wish to express my sincere congratulations on this milestone. The reason I am writing is to express my admiration for the song and to share some personal reflections that it inspired in me.
.
Listening to Hold On was a deeply emotional experience specially because your voice has a remarkable ability to evoke strong emotions. And, as I paid close attention to the lyrics too, I found myself reminiscing on a number of bittersweet memories from my own life. 
.
Iâ€™ve always had a deep love for dogs, inspired by Scooby-Doo in my childhood. Though I never had a pet, I cared for strays. One stray mother had a black pup I grew particularly attached to, & watching him grow into a beautiful young dog was a really rewarding experience. But one day life took a sad turn. I still remember that night. The clock was about to strike 9. I was on my terrace. As i turned around,at the exact moment, I caught the glimpse of a white SUV hi tting my stray with a full force. I couldn't register the reality of what I had seen. Boggled, I rushed to the scene, hoping it wasnâ€™t true, but found his lif eless body in a pool of bl ood. I was no longer a grown woman but an anguished soul, dev astated by the cru elty of that moment, bawling in the middle of the busy crossroad, disappointed in humanity. Three years later, I still canâ€™t walk that road without remembering what happened. But listening to 'Hold on' gives me hope and relief in ways I cannot explain. ( contd)

I do understand your strong & sincere desire to have a dog; I was once in the same position as you are now and I don't want to discourage you from getting one,  but I must say that it is very painful when they are gone and leave a void that cannot be filled. If I have understood you correctly, you are a deeply compassionate person, and I would never wish for any kind of pain to befall you. Ultimately, whether or not it happens will depend on your will power manifesting and the decision of forces in the Universe. Considering your own emotions, work schedule, and the dog's needs, I hope that you will make the best decision when the time comes. â˜ºï¸ğŸ‘
. 
Ending here, I would like to express my deepest gratitude for your contribution to such a beautiful and profound song. Your thoughtfulness in dedicating it to dog lovers is truly commendable. I sincerely hope that you will continue to be presented with meaningful opportunities and amazing songs in the future. Until my next letter, let us optimistically Hold On.

author: @Anastasia-x5m
text: My little dog passed away a week ago. This week was as an eden for me. He died at my 20's birthday day and i still can't move from this. My relatives say that it's "just a dog" but i can't explain and describe how much i love him. He was my safe place, my favorite friend and beloved animal, as a son. I love him unconditionally as him loved me and i can't stop crying since the day he dyed. This song is devasting for me and i want to thank you, because it's show me that i'm not the only who suffer, and it' not "just a dog", never was. Thank you for telling your story and open your feelings in this song, cause it have healing effects for persons like me. I will remember my dog forever and i hope in one day, he will run to me with a big smile and moving his tail as he do.

author: @ashaholic89
text:
Hey, today i miss my dogs, bella and mocha. I know its not fair for my current dogs, maxie and toshiro. But i cant help it.
I miss those 2 brats so much so often bc bella was the longest one to stay with me (19 years), and mocha was the bratty that always got on my nerves with his antics (8 years with me)

There is this saying that when our pets die, they will wait and greet us at the heaven's gate. I hope when i die, i still have the consciousness to meet and hug all my pets. Bella, mocha, lutfi, brenda of the dogs, a group of cats that i always named manis which means sweet (1 white with flip flop eyes, 1 light ginger, 2 white with mackarel spots, 1 calico), hamu and ninja the hamsters, cici the bunny, packs of ducks and chickens i didnt name that ended up chasing and harrasing me when i was a kid, a cute brazilian turtle, and a couple of old tortoises. Also some couple of louhan fish that love to be petted on their heads, but always ended the sweet moment with biting my little finger ğŸ˜ğŸ˜ğŸ˜

Aaaaa im crying. Being an adult is so hard and tiring ğŸ˜«ğŸ˜«ğŸ˜«ğŸ˜«ğŸ˜«ğŸ˜«

author: @jinko8185
text: I came back to this song after I lost my cat yesterday. he was by my side for 15 years, more than half of my life, and passed away while I was away. not having the chance to be close to him, to show him that I was with him in his last moments of suffering, is heartbreaking to me and everything seems to have become distressing and too painful to handle. I came back to this song because even though it's about a dog I hope that my heart, sooner or later, will be able to make the sadness fly away like dust in the wind, and that even if it still has to wait I hope that my little one will be a little more patient. It's hard and it hurts a lot. one day seungmin's voice and jisung's words will hopefully be able to give me the comfort I just can't find anywhere right now, nor when I'll go back home without him around.

author: @Aelitha-b9s
text: I love him.  I love him so much that my heart hurts.  Seungmin is so precious that I can't even believe that this person could exist.  I know he won't see it, but still, if there's a tiny chance... I love him.  it's not in a sexual way, god, of course not, it's not even in a romantic way!!  I'm not that delulu.  it's just like something that comes from the heart.. it's completely one sided platonic.  (if I meet him in real life, I will faint from everything, haha)) just Seungmin... many people say that he is a menace and slay, yes, he is, and I also like this part of him, but still.  .. he is one of the most sincere people I have ever seen.  I just melt when I see his smile.  his sadness.  his anger.  his disgust, his embarrassment.  It would seem that whatâ€™s wrong with these emotions, they are absolutely ordinary, but when itâ€™s Seungmin... it's something else.  it enters the heart and refuses to leave.  When he smiles, I also smile from ear to ear, when he cries... I cry too.  This is some completely new type of attachment.  Seungmin just... deserves everything in the world.  he's so... amazing.  I like absolutely everything about his body.  my heart and brain melt from his smile, just the sight of his joyful face brings such a strong release of endorphins into my blood that I almost suffocate.  I love his eyes, honestly.  they sparkle like real stars in the dark sky.  It seems to me that I am ready to look at them forever.  Seungmin is a gem.  It hurts me very much when I remember what he suffered.  Seungmin truly deserves the whole world and more.  so... I will try to be better to prove that this world deserves it too.  I will try to become better to be like him.  he motivates me like no one else.  Iâ€™m proud of him, so much so that Iâ€™m ready to shout at every corner how beautiful he is.  I'm afraid I'll never be able to leave him behind again.  he will forever be in my heart and in my head.  Otherwise it can not be.  he's just... the most amazing, the most amazing, the most... sparkling.  (can I use this word? English is not my first language, sorry) I will always love him.  and this absolutely does not depend on his external signs: from his hairstyle, from his weight, from his height, from his makeup, from his clothes, no, no, no.  his personality... I don't know him personally, but just looking at his eyes... the way his face lights up from the inside when he's with the members, at concerts or at fan meetings... you feel like you've known him all your life  .  Seungmin is warm.  it warms both the heart and soul.  I will always be for him, he will always be special to me, always loved.  I love you Kim Seungmin.  please don't give up.  you can always take a break if things get bad - and we will support you in difficult times.  we will offer our shoulders to you so that you can lean on them.  we will protect and keep you safe until you spread your wings and fly again.  and then... we will stretch out our hands to push you as high as possible.  because you deserve it like no one else.  I truly believe this.  and I am one hundred million percent sure that no one in the world can convince me.  I love you Kim Seungmin.  I have always loved, love and will always love.  please just be yourself.  you are an amazing person.  I'm proud to try to be like you.  you deserve everything.  and we will make every effort to ensure that you achieve what you deserve.  and you are worthy of only one thing - the top.  but only if you want to achieve it.  we will never put pressure on you.  so...please don't give up.  be healthy and most importantly, be happy.  Be yourself, Seungmini!  you are too precious to pretend to be someone else.  I love you.

author: @chirashii
text: I lost my childhood pup almost 2 years ago and I still breakdown when I think of her. She was the kindest, most loving dog a girl could ask for. I moved away from my childhood home and was only able to visit her once or twice a month. Still yet, she waited until the day I came to visit to say goodbye to me and pass on. It was heartbreaking, but Iâ€™m so thankful she gave me one more chance to kiss her, pet her, and tell her how much I love her. This song brings me comfort knowing this pain I feel is just a side effect of the immense love we had for each other. Candi, thanks for all youâ€™ve done for me. For being there for me thru all my highs and lows. I hope you can rest now, and wait for me until I can see you again <3

author: @liza_pet
text:
For so many years in K-POP, I haven't seen 
any beautiful and talented idols, but I can't 
even explain Seungmin in words. Truly, an angel whose beauty is created by heaven and sparkles brighter than the stars, eclipsing everything around, a voice as clear as crystal, gentle as a cloud and deeper than the ocean, which is only worth hearing and you are completely powerless before it. His voice is salvation and damnation at the same time, it is like a balm for the soul and warms your heart like the dearest person at the same time piercing your soul through, tearing apart, touching the farthest corners of your 
heart, leaving you "the way you are."

author: @serpentroad
text: I just lost my cat, which is my companion in cold and hard days, where it hurts to breathe and when sometimes when my anxieties got the better of me, he was always by my side. I know that opening my heart to love a cat after I lost three when I was a kid was a big and hard decision. I was aware about what to come if I decided to love him. But that foreknowledge doesn't help lessening the hurt when he was gone. Now, I have no nap buddy again, I had no one to snuggle on me or rubs against my legs. I had no 'him' that would climb my lap when I was home just to get pats (and prevent me from moving around) I miss him, so much. And now I seeks comfort from these kind of songs, and Hold On and Little Star helped me so much. Thank you, Jisung for writing this masterpiece. And thank you Seungmin for delivering the meaning of the song perfectly.

text: the lyrics, and seungmin's vocals... i have a cat a few years ago, he was so clingy, came to me snuggled whenever i'm around, he loved hugs, just the best cat someone ever asked for. he got sick, and before i got to bring him to the vet he went missing, and i never saw him again since. i blame myself for not taking care of him well when he's still here. i'm sorry seungmin but i can't listen to this song and not cry. but it's more like, a good cry now. thank you han & seungmin for this song ğŸ¥¹ğŸ¤

author: @ashaholic89
text:
This song reminds me of my precious baby. The name was Bella. It was june 2000 when i found her on a graveyard, she was tied and some guys said they wanted to eat her. But then my uncle gave them some money for her to be released. Then she went home with me. Btw, she picked her own name, Bella ğŸ˜‚
Since then she was a part of the family, and she was my best friend. We went through ups and downs. We also got punished together a lot because we did chaos in home ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚

She passed away in april 2019 due to old age. She couldnt see and hear any longer. She also had trouble walking. 
On her final days, she suddenly couldnt get up at all. Her last moment with me was so heart breaking. I knew it was her time to go, but i couldnt let her go. She hanged on and kept breathing eventhough her vessel was so fragile that even the slightest touch tore her skin. And still, she waited for me to send her away. About 5 minutes after i said, "Be, you can go if you its best for you. Dont mind me. I still have your brothers with me. Mocha and Maxie are here to accompany me.  Go to rainbow bridge and dont be sick anymore."
About a year and a half later, Mocha also left me to play and accompany Bella in rainbow bridge.

Man im still crying writing this ğŸ¥²

Anyway thank you seungmin and jisung for making this song. This will always remain in my heart, along with my memories and love for Bella and Mocha. Ah also Brenda and Lutfi, my previous dogs which left much much earlier than Bella.

author: @shekillalis5575
text:
Aku mau cerita.... 
Pertama makasih ke han udah buat lagu ini dan seungmin yang udah mau nyanyi lagu ini. 
Jadi lagu ini dirilis saat aku sedang down karena ini pertama kalinya aku merantau untuk kuliah gak diantar sama ortu. Jadi aku sempat homesick walaupun ada kakak juga disini namun tetap aja. Nah kebetulan aku adalah stay baru dan ngebiasin seungmin karena suaranya, dan merilis ini kemudian aku mendengarnya antara terharu, suka dan bangga sama suaranya, walau lagu ini tentang anjing tapi aku mengartikan yang lain dan itu membuatku terharu. 
Akan ku ingat lagu ini teruss....

author: @cocofruta0
text:
I want to thank Han and Seungmin for Hold on and those heartbreaking lyrics. I know its late but I wasn't brave enough to write this earlier because then it would mean it's real. My 16 years old dog is very sick and I don't think she's gonna make it, I've spent most of my life with her and she means the world to me. But this song is helping me a lot in some way during the process and it will help me in the future I'm sure. It's not being easy for me and right now I feel like everything is coming down on me but I'll keep going as many people have already done. Thanks again from the bottom of my heart.
Thanks for making music

author: @bluecat-143
text: this song means so much to me. about 3 years ago i lost my first dog, the morning when i woke up i started searching for her in the house and then i saw that the front door was open so since i used to live in a very small village and i knew everyone there i started looking for her. an hour passed, i went back home, when i got there my mom told me that the dog was missing for several hours and that she had already looked for it before i woke up. i started crying cause i knew someone had probably poisoned her and threw her body away so we couldn't find her.( a very common phenomenon considering where i used to live). i never saw the dog again. that day i remember crying my heart out and screaming, that dog had really helped with my mental health and after i lost her during summer time i wasn't able to do anything i wouldn't get off bed not to go to the toilet not to even eat, i was looking forward to dying. eventually fall  came and school started so i had no choice but to get off  bed and activate myself. now after 3 years i still think about her a lot but she brings joy to my heart and the painful memories are slowly fading away. that song really portraits the feeling of loosing your dog, some may treat them like regular animals but they could also become your family and you want to hold on them as long as possible. thank han jisung for this masterpiece and seungmin for signing this so beautifullyğŸ©·ğŸ©·

author: @dinagram
text:
As a person with 3 dogs and another one already gone, I have to say that losing a pet is devastating. It's like losing a family member. But that family member can't understand words, so you have to show them that you love them but it never feels enough. Even at their final  moment, while you're crying for them, they're trying to ease your pain. They're trying to reach out to you to understand why you're sad.
 Having a pet is the purest form of unconditional love you could have ever asked for.

author: @elintenable1262
text: My childhood dog died a bit less than a year ago when I was living at my uni dorm. My family decided not to tell me because they were scared it would mess up my semester, so when I learned about his passing, everyone had already moved on. I've always had something blocking me from living my grief since everyone was already done living theirs. This song had only been out for a few days, but it's already allowed me to be sad about it and cry, and just grief in a more healthy way. Thank you, Han and Seungmin, for this song.

author: @stillastrayyayayaya
text: This song means so much to me. It resonates with me on a much deeper level. On the one hand, since the song is dedicated to all dogs, I couldn't help but think about my own dog who recently had a seizure. She is fine now but since she is ageing, I am gripped with the fear of losing my first dog. On the other hand, the lyrics reminded me of someone who had only just come into this world when life was taken away from him in 2020. I miss him truly and deeply. Thank you Hannie and Minnie for this heartfelt song. It's cathartic to listen to. Will support Stray Kids forever! â¤ï¸

author: @jeejeesock
text: Finally,we were able to hear with our own ears a masterpiece prepared by our incredibly talented and capable boys â€” Seungmin and Han. From the very first note, this song penetrates into the very soul and warms even in the coldest periods. The truly unique sound,the unspeakably Seungmin amazing vocals, the message conveyed by the guys and the meaning of the song really fascinates and motivates for something much more. This song was addressed to deceased pets, as evidenced by its translation. It is such a pity that a huge number of people have experienced such heavy losses. Anyway, I sincerely believe that now their pets are in a better world, having finally found their peace. Absolutely every pet brings certain colors to the life of its owner, unwittingly making him at times happier than ever. To be honest, I really am still very impressed. How sincere and tender songs our guys write is so surprising. They make their own way and create their own, truly unique and incomparable story, shaking the whole industry and winning the hearts of each of their listeners. Words are not enough to describe all my love, devotion and gratitude to these amazing and amazing guys, so I just want to thank them once again absolutely for everything they create with their own hands, for their endless love, support and care, so helping out in the most difficult times and just for that they exist and make our lives much happier and better. We will always stay by your side and support each of you in absolutely any of your business and endeavors. Please shine as brightly,continue to go forward as boldly, not allowing any difficulties and adversities to lead you astray from your path and take care of yourselfğŸ¥°

author: @okiizawazii2777
text:
Still shock with the meaning tho... every listen to this song, i cry (and still crying) because i remember about my patients and my pet. I'm a veterinarian , a dog and cat lover, and an owner too... i know how it feels when i have to say that their pet didn't have much time or they're no need  to feel the pain any longer (means it's better to put them to sleep). Well, i should give the owner explanation about their true condition and i can feel their emotion too when the owner looks their pet. Even their eyes talk to each other and it moves me. And i can say, that their bond sometimes feels like soulmate... it's crazy, but it's true! And sometimes when their bond is really really deep... i realize that in the future, that will be me in that situation... because our pet lives so they can be sick, can be old and then died. All we can do is being prepared with give them the best care, love and make sure their well-being is good.

This is the most emotional song i've heard... thank you seungmin, thank you han jisung, thank you bangchan and everyone who made this song perfectly for an owner like meâ¤

I give my love to all owners who have pets. Hug them and love them dearly, because we never know when the time comesâ¤

author: @Esma-yb8od
text: Honestly, I never had a dog but the lyrics are so well written that I could almost feel the emotion even though I never felt it, and see the animal even though I never had one. This song is really sad but it makes you think of those sad thoughts as just memories you'll never forget and that's why I love about Stray Kids. They know how to talk about unhappy things in a way that still keeps you smiling and thinking positive. It's not about loosing your dog or any animal directly but in my opinion it's beyond this loss, it's the feeling you remember, and the memories you keep to hold on until you see them again. And this is really deep because people keep telling me to live in the moment. You can't be self conscious about everything everyday and it's when you loose precious things that you realise their importance, right? But I realised recently that I don't think living in the present is about thinking about living in the present and being conscious about everything that happens when you're living a happy moment with your friends for exemple. I think now that it's about the memories you hold onto. Because if you live in the present with the fear of loosing what you have, you can't truly live with them at the same timeline and make the most out of those persons/moments. So we should live carelessly, still enjoying every moment, but stop focusing on 'living in the present'. We'll enjoy those moments even more in our memories, that's also part of living in the present, and that's okay. I don't know if this made any sense but I wrote this to express myself about those worries I had and that this song made me think of. So thank you Seungmin for this, and everyone that have might worked on this song as well. Your voice is amazing, and the song is really unique. I love you. Stay safe. I'll be enjoying every second I listen to this song and keep it as good memories for the futur. I will never forget about you.

author: @FingerFeetVitamins
text: I know this is about a dog but I couldn't stop thinking of my cat that I had since birth who passed many years ago, I didn't give him a proper goodbye because at the time I wouldn't let myself cry or show much emotion. I'd never seen my dad cry which led me to believe crying was weak. This cat was an angel sent to save my family, when I was just a baby he would lay next to me if I cried. He was always comforting us whether we were sad or even just when he shared the happy times with us. I now have a cat that reminds me so much of him. She wakes me up in the morning and follows me to the bathroom, she lays at my feet as I write this. To my beloved angel, rest in peace. I can't wait to see you again, Norm.â¤

author: @alixgorgas4589
text: Back in April, my dog had passed away. He was my best friend. He was the only thing that could make me happy when I was struggling most. I loved him more than anything and I miss him everyday. Today when I listened to this song for the first time and seen what the meaning of this song was, I cried. I cried so hard. I would do anything to be able to see my dog again, my sweet angel. To see him run to the door to greet me after my long band practices, to cuddle with me when I have had a bad day. This song gave me a sense that he will always be with me no matter where he is and I have found a comfort in this song that I could never find in another. I hope others can find that same comfort in this song as well. Thank you Seungmin. Thank you Stray Kids. Thank you for helping me find my emotions again through your music.

text: My dog just died a few weeks ago, he was just happily wagging his tail as usual at that time but when it was night, he suddenly looked hurt and sad. author: @klaudiaszemeredi7295
text: When I first heard the song, my first thought was that this song might be about stay and skz connection. But when I listened to it again, I got the sudden feeling that "oh.. this might be about losing someone. Like a dog. This might be about losing my dog.." This made me tear up as a listened to it again with this new meaning. But after I scrolled down to see who wrote the song, I saw Han's name. I suddenly got so emotional that I started crying. "I would have known.." This was my first reaction when I saw his name. Seungmin was a perfect choice for this song, the emotions came through very well. The other thing that made me cry is that I realized how much deep emotion Han carries with him. He has such deep feelings that it is probably very difficult for him to talk about, or he cannot tell them at all. And that's exactly why he expresses them through songs. This truly made me cry. Thank you <3

author: @judethefourth336
text:
Having an old dog who has been with my since my childhood, through my adolescence and the start of my adult life... this song brought me to tears. Seungmin's voice is so warm and calms my shattered heart by the thought of that, one day, sooner than I want to, my best tiny friend will no longer be by my side. Thank you Han Jisung also for writing these beautiful lyrics. Both of you, all of Stray Kids, are always able to heal the wounds of my soul and express the feelings I never have the correct words for. Thank you once again. I love you, and I love you my little fluffy friend, I hope we can stay together for more years to come ğŸ’—

Edit: I just lost him yesterday and there is this incredibly huge hole carved on my chest. I feel so empty and devoid of energy. He was my sunshine. I spent some of his last hours for the whole night with him until we could bring him to the vet. I can't still believe it's real. I still hope to see him sleeping in his bed. But this songs says what I desire, to one day be reunited with him, see him again full of youthful energy, happy and with full mobility. I want to hold him in my arms forever.

author: @nobody23.12
text:
I don't know how to express what I feel. so I'll just try to tell the story.

Recently my dog â€‹â€‹passed away. she was already 13 or 14, can't remember. I knew her all my life, so I didnâ€™t understand how important she was to me in full. she just lived with us like, idk, my older sister? 
one day I was practicing a new program (I am a pianist). my father came into my room with the words "Daffy died." I didn't believe him so I ran into the yard (Daffy lived in a booth, she was quite large). At first I didn't understand why my dad was trying to stop me. then I realized... Daffy was laying under our dogwood tree. without breathing. I rushed to my room, dad behind me. but there was nothing on my face at all. I was just waiting for him to leave. 
I was in such shock. nothing foreshadowed a trouble. she ran and play as always, ate well... I was able to keep my face until my father left. but as soon as the door closed, I started silently crying.

I haven't shed a tear in the past year and a half (Daffy passed away on 03/23/22). I didn't cry at all, even when I was alone. Didnt laugh or smth. just living. It was as if strong emotions had been turned off in me, idk. my maximum is to smile at a joke or mourn under the series. Even my mom wanted to put me in a psychiatric hospital for a while, just becausr i changed so much "just because of a dog".

Now Im crying. I myself was a little confused when felt a lump in my throat. But I cried! Thank you so much Seungmin and Han for this! Lately i've really begun to believe that I'm not capable of such emotions anymore.

I didn't even know the translation of the song, seriously. When I saw it, I cried even harder. maybe it's because I'm like 3? years old stan Skz and I subconsciously understand some phrases. maybe (most likely) because of Seungmin's emotion in his voice, I don't know...


just thank you for making me cry (sounds weird doesn't it haha). For the first time in a year, I feel relatively alive. love you. Thank you.


sorry for being sloppy in the comments. if you don't like it, reply to the comment, I'll read it and delete it, no problem.

Thank you. Sorry.

author: @bekka99
text:
do you know what is a beautiful feeling? knowing that i right now am moved to tears by this incredible song alongside many more stays. i can feel it in my heart. many of us are crying at the same time, and if not crying then still so incredibly moved by the extremely touching lyrics, by the beautiful music and by our beloved min's angelic voice blessing us once again. 

all my love goes to every stay who can relate to this song, you're not alone my love. â¤ my dear hannie, neither are you. stay will always be right here with you honey. â¤ the pain of losing a beloved pet is... soul wrenching, heart breaking. thank you for writing this song. a song we can turn to when we experience that pain ourselves, when we reminisce about our past beloved pets. thank you jisung, thank you chan, thank you seungmin, thank you versachoi, thank you nickko young.

tw: death

to end this off, i woke up today after a horrible nightmare, it was about death, about losing my mother, she's sick so i'm scared. the nightmare was scarily realistic and the crappy feeling it brought me has been lingering all day. at the same time i'm scared of losing my cat, as she is getting old. her time is near, no matter how deeply i wish it wasn't. this entire day has passed by in a blur. but this song, that i've spent who knows how long listening to on repeat by now, helped bring out the tears that have been needing to come out. the timing of this song being released is scarily accurate to my personal situation, to when i need it the most. but who's surprised, stray kids came into my life two years and three months ago at a time where i needed them. it's only fitting this song does the same.
thank you again. i'm going to keep this song near and dear to my heart. i can always count on stray kids to help me feel better in tough times. thank you, i love you deeply. â¤

author: @bekka99
text:
wow... this hit home. this really hit home. i'm currently terrified of losing my cat, she's getting quite old now, so it's constantly on my mind that she might not be here with me for much longer. seeing that han wrote this song released the tears that were trying to escape, i got some much needed crying done. thank you han, thank you for sharing this piece of your soul with us. thank you channie and versachoi for helping composing it, and nickko young for helping arrange it, and deeply thank you seungminnie for singing your beautiful heart out and blessing us with your vocals. your voice soothes my soul and brings me peace. there are no words in existence that could ever describe just how truly beautiful your voice is. you have the voice of an angel, and you are stay's angel minnie. 

han, you never fail to amaze me with your writing. you truly have a gift, yet, at the same time, it's so clear that you work endlessly hard to be this incredible and to keep growing as an artist. we can see it, stay sees your hard work paying off. with every song you share with us i get more inspired to work hard for my dreams. with every song you share with us you heal another piece of my heart, another piece of my soul. you make me feel heard, feel seen, feel understood. i'm beyond lucky that i get to witness the beautiful results of your hard work time and time again, lucky that i get to see a little part of your heart. you mean so much to me my dear jisung. stays love you so much.

the song is on repeat while it's pouring rain outside, while my lights are off. i'm just sitting here in my feelings processing everything. i've lost sight of how much time has passed, how many times i've listened to the song now. the rain knew it was time to rain when i listened first, it's perfect while listening to this masterpiece of a song. the only "problem" i have right now is i want to listen to the song while wearing headphones, but then i can't hear the rain. xD such a hard problem, i know. :P

once again, thank you for this masterpiece hannie. han your writing is some of the most beautiful art that has ever been and ever will be. i'm so beyond grateful that i get to be your fan and witness the greatness that is han jisung. aaand here comes the tears again haha, i'm just so eternally grateful, thankful, that i get to live at the same time as you, be the same age as you and go through life parallel with you. i will forever be by your side, by chan's, by minnie's and all of our wonderful boys' sides. thank you stray kids for being here, for being born, for sharing your passion with us. thank you. i love you, more than i could ever say, more than i could ever properly convey. i hope you are able to feel mine and all of stays love to you in some way.

when my baby, my cat, ascends the rainbow bridge i will find great comfort in this song, as well as jinnie's "i miss you". i am truly lucky that i get to turn to my stray kids when i'll be going through tough times in my life. i can never say it enough: i'm eternally grateful to be a stay, and eternally grateful to you. thank you. all the love to you my dearest stray kids.

stray kids everywhere all around the world. you're going to keep growing and enrich more people's lives because you are here, because you exist, because of you sharing your dreams and beautiful work with the world. i hope all eight of you feel the same amount of happiness through you life that you've brought me, because it has been an endless amount. 
i love you.

I love and miss you, Jacky <3

author: @noeasyshyba
text: I really wasn't Prepared for this song when I started listening to it. It's a beautiful song that caused me to start crying a lot about half way through because maybe a month after I found Stray Kids and became a Stay, I lost my Dog that has been in the Family for 12 years. It was a really hard time and still struggle with missing him sometimes. These Lyric.. they really capture that feeling and the thoughts I think when I miss him, even in the way it says closing their eyes for the last time.. I still cry a lot when I come home after a while and he isn't there at the door wagging his tail like the Song says. So, thank you for this beautiful song that brings me a kind of sad comfort.

author: @ellieh136
text:
Seungmin, sir, I'm gonna need you to stop making me cry so much, please and thank you (keep it up, they're good tears). You already blow me away every day with yourself and your voice (which I'm so glad you get to share with the world! It's so well deserved), but this song.... You did an amazing job on this. It's so beautiful. And Han did such an amazing job on the lyrics. I really felt both of your passions through your voice, and his lyrics. I have lost three dogs in my lifetime so far. The first one was my soul dog. My best friend while i was growing up. One of the very few constants in my life. Losing him was like losing a piece of me. The second, passed away suddenly while I was away at university. I didn't even get to say goodbye, and that tears me apart every single day. The third, I didn't have him for a long time, only a few days, but I was so connected to him. He hasn't passed away, I just wasn't in a position to keep him, and in order to give him the life he deserves, I had to give him up, but I think about him every single day. So this song hits so so hard for me. Thank you for such a beautiful gift, Minnie. I want you to know that it is seen, it is heard, and it is appreciated <3
All my love <3

author: @rieandrique
text:
Listening to this and hearing the lyrics get me sobbing, my tears won't stop, like at all. I've also recently just lost my fur baby that literally saved my life because I was going through so damn much, and because of them being gone, I genuinely thought I was going to lose myself again. If it weren't for the babies that they left behind (although two of them are now resting peacefully somewhere up there), I would've been gone.

Which is why listening to this song is giving me so much comfort through the tears because of how much I can relate to it. Additionally, Seungmin's voice is so so good and so so angelic, I can tell why Hannie wanted Seungmin to be the one to sing this (our puppy boi Seungs). Thank you so much for a womderful SKZ-RECORD! Love this one so much

author: @mikacasquejo
text:
I have an old dog and for the next weeks, i have to leave her home with the rest of my family and live near the university I'm studying at. The thing is, I know this dog to the bone. I'm the only one who will be able to read and understand her expressions and actions. My family can barely take care of her. I have to beg them to give her attention. No matter how many times I asked them if i could bring her with me, they said no because the electricity will increase, and keep giving me stupid reasons, mostly financially.

A dog, unlike to other people, is more than a dog. They're more than just for entertainment, more than a friend, a soulmate, or an emotional support. For me, my dog's my lifeline. She's old and I want to give her the best last years she deserves. But unfortunately, I'm just a kid who loved her so deeply and sometimes I despise my age for not being able to take care of her the way I want to. This song resonates.

author: @H6vftkk
text: I think everyone focused only on Sungmin's voice and did not really focus on the depth of the lyrics. If you delve deeper into understanding the meaning of the song, you will find that it carries all the feelings that Sungmin and stray kids  with STAYS in their journey. At the beginning of the song, he describes how Stays were supporting and holding on to stray kids and they were a source of hope for them, and then as if he was saying to stays with them until after the end and forever, and to stick to them as in the first place, even if many years have passed, and no matter how old and how old they are. Age and no matter how far they are away from us..., â¤this song really touched my heart and made me think, will the stray kids  and the stays still love each other as they are now, even after the end of the band's contract, even after many years have passed???

author: @madewlyne
text:
Thank you stray kids 

It's weird, losing her one day was weird. It's been three months since I last saw her, since I cried like a little girl because I couldn't say goodbye to her. It still hurts.

Losing a pet is something that has happened before and I hate the feeling. Thanks for this song, I was able to find solace because I felt pathetic to miss her and to think what it would have been like if she looked at me with her big eyes.

I miss her and I hope that when we meet again she will be as happy to see me as I am to her <3


I'm sorry if you don't understand, I don't speak English lol

i hope you're happy in puppy heaven, my love.

text:
this is making me cry. 

My only cat, who always sleeps by my side every day, died a few weeks ago. I'm devastated, and I cried all day. The memories we make together are so precious to me that I am still sad. His photos on my phone are the only thing I have that I can keep forever. Now that I'm away from home and my cats, I'm gradually losing energy in the activities I most enjoy.  They are the ones who give me courage. 

This song just perfectly expresses how I feel. 

i love you, seiji! 
thank you, han, seungmin, and chann for creating such a heartwarming and good song. <3

And the fact that he wrote this beautiful song for Bbama is even more amazing, because it's not that common for songwriters to write songs about their pets (another beautiful one, for Kkami, is Little Star by Hyunjinie) ... And now that my dog, that I raised by myself (I adopted her when she was 3 months old circa, from an abandoned litter) , I took her in a couple of months after I started to live by myself... Now I am 30 and she is 10... And it makes me cry the only thought of her leaving me one day... So this song (and Little Star) makes me tear up a lot.... Beautiful, thank you for blessing us with your emotional and awesome lyricism, Hannie, thank you for blessing us with your beautiful music, Channie, thank you for blessing us with your unique, amazing, honey voice, Seungminie. Thank you for this other masterpiece, you always give us nothing less than masterpieces. â¤â¤â¤

three weeks ago my best friend, my first dog, passed away. He was with me for 13 years, since I was 12, the last year he was struggling with kidneys disease, he was getting weaker every month and at the end we decided to release him from this pain. It was the hardest decision to make and I could not be next to him for his last moments, I was in other town and couldnâ€™t get back on time. This is why Iâ€™ll probably feel guilty for the rest of my life. I couldnâ€™t talk with anyone about it and cried only once, at the day, when itâ€™s happened, after that I feel like everything inside me froze, crashed and now there is huge hole. I felt like I couldnâ€™t release my emotions at all and it was hidden somewhere deep inside. But from the first line of this song I was able to release emotions at last. Iâ€™m still crying. I donâ€™t know at all how to get over this, but at least I guess

text: i lost my dog a few months ago, it was shocking and i was the one who found it, i grew up with my dog, we shared so many memories together, i tried my best to make his life the best i could afford, until one day he just wasn't here anymore, my life was torned, changed completely but everyone around me seemed fine, i tought i might be overreacting, but while i'm writing this in tears i can finally understand that i lost my family, it's so hard to try to get back in life when you feel like you can't, eventually i did, i had to keep studying for college and all but i couldn't had done it without stray kids, i'm so gald that i had the luck to meet this guys years ago because everytime i feel alone or that i can't do it anymore they come to the rescue, i love you guys so much, and thank you kim seungmin for writing this beautiful song, and understand the love between humans and dogs, i love you forever my little puppy â¤ï¸â€ğŸ©¹

author: @SakkaraKirax
text:
Seungmin, sweet puppy... was Hyunjin's Little Star not enough? I am a full-grown adult now sobbing over my best friend, Sandy, that I lost over 15 years ago. That good boy literally saved my life by getting help when I wasn't breathing and got me through some terrible times, right by my side. Having to say goodbye to him after 18 years of him in my life is still one of the hardest things I've ever done. 

Seungmin, your voice brings emotion to life like none other. It was beautiful, and I'm going to be inconsolable for the rest of the day. I'm sorry to anyone who has felt the pain of losing a beloved pet.

author: @Shespider
text:
Yes Seungmin is a Beautiful Singer with a lovely voice but those lyrics? I use the translation, yes, but listen to the korean flow? The choise of words, the interlinked themes - not only is the meaning something most of us can relate to one way or another, but every part of this arragement is perfectly thought out to create this emotional crescendo, matching the chorus lyrics perfectly - from pyring fire to roaring to ashes.... Also the thought of the once welcoming sight of a happy loved one waiting and now it's only the light again and only the hope of a next meeting in the distant future remains - 
I'm at relistening number three, and I can't find the words. Thank you. Thank you for writing this. Thank you for sharing this. Thank you.
